				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Each cpu cycle is broken down into two phases: an operation then a memory access, in that order. If the opcode does not have to access memory on its last cycle, it will pre-fetch the next opcode. This makes some instructions appear to be one cycle shorter than they really are.
<br />
<br />There's no need to re-fetch the opcode, or use it from a cache. Execution of the next opcode will begin immediately as if the two opcodes overlapped on that one cycle.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

