						<div class="postbody">I am not sure of the hardware behavior myself, but most emus I see deals with it by just reading the address (pc) twice. in case of SEI, it would read PC for the opcode, then PC++ and then throw it away. This shouldn't really matter except for timing purposes. I don't think anyone would be crazy enough to point PC to an address of a memory mapped register. If they did, it would just be for testing accuracy purposes, rather than getting a game to run.</div>

